The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 30 November is 9,098 (1,053 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 25 November, there were 579 new confirmed cases (67.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 November, there were 1,022 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 43% (443 fewer cases).
